[30;1m19 | [0m[35m  * A major feature addition is to allow the user to choose how the[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m    event listener is implemented. The default is for the event[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    listener to use the requests library and run in a thread. This[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    update allows the user to run the event listener using the[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    twisted.internet library, by setting the ``config.EVENTS_MODULE``[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    module to point to the :py:mod:`soco.events_twisted` module. See[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m    the example in events_twisted.[0m
